This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video instance segmentation, which is a task in computer vision. The use of a 3D causal convolutional network also suggests that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as this type of network is commonly used in robotics applications. The use of self-supervised learning for depth estimation suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of real-time performance suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
